flavor_text_entries.diamond:
It sprays a vile-smelling fluid
from the tip of its tail to attack.
Its range is over 160 feet.
flavor_text_entries.pearl:
It sprays a stinky fluid from its
tail. The fluid smells worse the
longer it is allowed to fester.
flavor_text_entries.platinum:
It attacks by spraying a horribly
smelly fluid from the tip of its tail.
Attacks from above confound it.
flavor_text_entries.heartgold:
It attacks by spraying a repugnant
fluid from its tail, but the stench
dulls after a few squirts.

flavor_text_entries.sword:
In its belly, it reserves stinky fluid that it shoots
from its tail during battle. As this Pokémon’s diet
varies, so does the stench of its fluid.
flavor_text_entries.shield:
It digs holes in the ground to make its nest.
The stench of the fluid it lets fly from the tip
of its tail is extremely potent.
flavor_text_entries.legends-arceus:
Sprays a poisonous fluid to take down prey. Sometimes, unable
to stomach the stench of its own fluid, it leaves the bested
prey uneaten.
